	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Sep 22nd 6:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is my first post to this forum, but since I am a Premium member now, I guess yill see more of me. <br><br>Triggered effect off this robe is exceptional.&nbsp;&nbsp;Everything in game is there for a reason.  For those that knock this effect being a long cast time, fail to see the actual uses this is best for.  This is not the effect to cast during everyday play.  This is a "UBER" encounter type of proc.  Last night, my guild in PoG fought Treah long enough for me to nuke to OOM and sit to med to FULL then nuke to finish.  With a fight lasting that long, I could have just used this robes proc, then switched to a Draught as soon as it hit 40 percent. Why do this? AGGRO, if your only casting every 30 seconds by default. Your aggro is far far less than chain casting a lure or Draughts.  Why would I be satisfied with this effect, I am doing damage to the target.  Damage that adds up for sure.  Then I am like a loaded artillary brigade as soon as NUKE is called.  That means I would have full mana to take care of those pesky little Protectors of Growth that show up. For those of you that think they are tough..hahaha.  They are mince meat with good tanks.  <br><br>Back to the point, this robe is good for those encounters that would otherwise be a pain in the butt to try and sit during.  Temple of Veeshan is an example. Try sitting during an AE barage.  With this robe, your doing damage waiting like a crouched lion to unleash that 2500mana bomb on the mob.  Don't flame this cast time until you have thought about all the uses. I applaud Verant for making it long. That way I don't have to concentrate so much on keeping aggro of me.  Just clicky clicky till NUKE is called.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
