	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was lucky enough to get my Sorcerer's Robe last night, after spending 18 hours in the Plane of Growth.&nbsp;&nbsp;It dropped off of 'an Entoling Essence Conduii'.  Its a level 60 mob that casts Complete Healing on itself, and is VERY hard to interupt.  That same mob dropped Magician's pants also, so it seems likely that it drops the major int caster's pieces.<br><br>The Sorcerer's Robe is identical to the quested version from Thurgadin.  The only difference is in the appearence.  The quested versions from Kael and Skyshrine are both a little better than the Sorcerer's Robe...but I'm not complaining ;)<br><br>The Enticement of Flame effect is nice, but limited.  For those that don't know, it is a level 44 Wizard spell that does 360 of nearly unresistable fire damage.  The casting time is a full 30 seconds, and you can not do anything else while its casting except move...no inviting party members, no checking inventory, no going to your spellbook.  Luckily, the /sit and /sit off commands do work, so you can effectively med while you cast this spell, just make sure that you hit /sit off before the spell casting is finished.  There is no Casting Time meter when you use the robe, so you have to judge the timing for yourself.<br><br>Good luck everyone on getting their robes too...<br>&nbsp;<br>Alavair Eldritch<br>54th Channeler of Solusek Ro<br>Furious Pantaloons</td></tr>
